rica before the mid-1960s.An examination of the inputs of African and French governments into post-independence developments North and South of the Sahara.A historical survey of the two major tendencies in African film production over the past 40 years.A detailed analysis of the work of five talented young filmmakers, representative of those born since independence."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMotion picture industryzAfrica. 0aMotion pictureszAfrica. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074862123140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748628063?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748628063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748628063/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK